The paper deals with information theory and coding, specifically with the construction of polar codes and polar lattices for extracting Wyner's common information in lossless and lossy Gray-Wyner problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of polar lattices for quantization, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with Gaussian sources and multiple sources, which could fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of test channels and achieving best-known regions, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
